It's like saying kinetic energy
plus potential energy is a

00:43:41.464 --> 00:43:43.897
constant.
It's not a constant you can

00:43:43.897 --> 00:43:46.120
look up in a book.
It depends on what your

00:43:46.120 --> 00:43:48.672
particle is doing.
But for that particle in those

00:43:48.672 --> 00:43:51.879
conditions, kinetic with
potential adds to a particular

00:43:51.879 --> 00:43:55.264
constant we call total energy.
Likewise, PV to the

00:43:55.264 --> 00:43:57.949
γ is a constant for this
particular gas.

00:43:57.949 --> 00:44:06.250
Okay, so all this is actually a
preparation for something else.

00:44:06.250 --> 00:44:09.989
And that's what we are going to
discuss now.

00:44:09.989 --> 00:44:14.960
So, between now and the end of
this course we are going to

00:44:14.960 --> 00:44:18.710
discuss the Second Law of
Thermodynamics.

00:44:23.110 --> 00:44:25.730
So, we have done all we want to
do with the First Law.

00:44:25.730 --> 00:44:30.168
So, you guys should be able to
be given various graphs on the

00:44:30.168 --> 00:44:33.035
PV plane,
find the work done in going

00:44:33.035 --> 00:44:35.651
from here to there,
find the change in internal

00:44:35.651 --> 00:44:39.059
energy,
find the heat added and so on.

00:44:39.059 --> 00:44:41.639
I hope you can do such
problems, but they're all going

00:44:41.639 --> 00:44:44.343
to be one of these formulas.
Say there's going to be

00:44:44.343 --> 00:44:47.369
adiabatic or constant pressure
or constant temperature,

00:44:47.369 --> 00:44:50.747
so you just plug the numbers
in, keep track of the signs by

00:44:50.747 --> 00:44:53.369
using common sense.
Alright.

00:44:53.369 --> 00:44:56.271
So now, we come to the last
part of thermodynamics,

00:44:56.271 --> 00:44:59.057
which is to me one of the most
beautiful parts of

00:44:59.057 --> 00:45:02.976
thermodynamics,
which starts out with asking

00:45:02.976 --> 00:45:07.262
the following question.
There are certain things in

00:45:07.262 --> 00:45:11.006
this world that are perfectly
allowed but don't seem to

00:45:11.006 --> 00:45:15.490
happen.
Let's take many examples.

00:45:15.490 --> 00:45:18.493
Take the Joule experiment.
You take a cylinder of water

00:45:18.493 --> 00:45:21.833
with a paddle that can spin and
you put some weight around the

00:45:21.833 --> 00:45:25.270
pulley and the weight goes down.
Paddle spins;

00:45:25.270 --> 00:45:28.862
the water heats up.
You take a movie of that,

00:45:28.862 --> 00:45:33.550
and the movie is so fine it can
even catch individual molecules.

00:45:33.550 --> 00:45:38.530
Now, you play the movie
backwards.

00:45:38.530 --> 00:45:41.623
So, you watch the movie being
played back and what do you

00:45:41.623 --> 00:45:44.128
find?
Suddenly, the weight starts

00:45:44.128 --> 00:45:48.602
moving up, paddle spins the
other way, and the water cools

00:45:48.602 --> 00:45:51.264
down.
This is not in violation of any

00:45:51.264 --> 00:45:54.808
of the laws you have learned
including the First Law of

00:45:54.808 --> 00:45:58.717
Thermodynamics,
because when the weight went

00:45:58.717 --> 00:46:04.563
down and the water heated up,
some amount of work was done on

00:46:04.563 --> 00:46:07.622
the water,
and the energy of the water

00:46:07.622 --> 00:46:09.579
went up.
In the reverse process,

00:46:09.579 --> 00:46:13.124
the energy of the water went
down and instead the weight went

00:46:13.124 --> 00:46:15.370
up, so work was done by the
system.

00:46:15.370 --> 00:46:20.735
But that doesn't seem to happen.
If the weight comes down you

00:46:20.735 --> 00:46:23.138
can wait all day.
Well, let me give you another

00:46:23.138 --> 00:46:24.936
example.
Take a chunk of wood,

00:46:24.936 --> 00:46:28.550
you slide it there.
Sorry.

00:46:28.550 --> 00:46:32.179
It was not a piece of wood and
it didn't stop.

00:46:32.179 --> 00:46:35.665
See, this is why I don't do
demonstrations because even the

00:46:35.665 --> 00:46:38.670
simplest demonstration I have
done doesn't work.

00:46:38.670 --> 00:46:41.550
So, that's why some of us
become theoretical physicists.

00:46:41.550 --> 00:46:45.129
I did a demonstration where
some trolley is supposed to

00:46:45.129 --> 00:46:48.161
shoot a little marble.
All the marble had to do was

00:46:48.161 --> 00:46:50.683
come down and even that didn't
work, so I don't do

00:46:50.683 --> 00:46:52.780
demonstrations.
Well, let's try this.

00:46:52.780 --> 00:46:55.115
Here's an eraser,
and give it a push and it

00:46:55.115 --> 00:46:57.450
stops.
Take the movie of that.

00:46:57.450 --> 00:47:00.725
Play it backwards.
You will find suddenly,

00:47:00.725 --> 00:47:03.789
you know the table heats up a
little bit due to friction.

00:47:03.789 --> 00:47:06.909
The table can cool down and the
eraser can move backwards

00:47:06.909 --> 00:47:10.050
picking up speed [laughter].
Right.

00:47:10.050 --> 00:47:12.176
So, why did we laugh?
You have no reason to laugh

00:47:12.176 --> 00:47:14.349
right now because it doesn't
violate anything you have

00:47:14.349 --> 00:47:16.491
learned,
other than your daily

00:47:16.491 --> 00:47:20.920
experience, because in the
reverse process every atom,

00:47:20.920 --> 00:47:24.450
you know, every atomic thing on
the desk that started moving,

00:47:24.450 --> 00:47:26.151
is made to stop,
turn around,

00:47:26.151 --> 00:47:28.130
and move in the backwards
direction.

00:47:28.130 --> 00:47:31.587
And every collision between
atoms on the desk and atoms on

00:47:31.587 --> 00:47:34.559
the eraser will obey all the
laws of mechanics.

00:47:34.559 --> 00:47:38.148
For example,
if you have a planet going

00:47:38.148 --> 00:47:42.398
around the Sun,
if you stop the planet and you

00:47:42.398 --> 00:47:46.726
reverse the velocity,
it will go the opposite way and

00:47:46.726 --> 00:47:50.152
the opposite motion is in
complete accord with Newton's

00:47:50.152 --> 00:47:52.001
laws.
In fact, there may be somewhere

00:47:52.001 --> 00:47:54.640
a solar system where the planet
actually goes the other way.

00:47:54.640 --> 00:47:58.222
It doesn't violate anything.
So, in all the movies which are

00:47:58.222 --> 00:48:00.986
played backwards,
at the very microscopic level

00:48:00.986 --> 00:48:03.750
there's nothing that says it
cannot happen,

00:48:03.750 --> 00:48:06.872
and yet it does not happen.
Here's another thing that does

00:48:06.872 --> 00:48:10.182
not happen.
I take a box and I put some gas

00:48:10.182 --> 00:48:15.318
molecules on one side and
there's a partition holding them

00:48:15.318 --> 00:48:18.709
in that side.
Then I remove this partition

00:48:18.709 --> 00:48:22.720
and I wait a little bit;
then I know the gas fills up.

00:48:27.360 --> 00:48:29.780
That's like perfume leaking out
of the bottle.

00:48:29.780 --> 00:48:32.260
Now, take a movie of these
molecules.

00:48:32.260 --> 00:48:35.606
When they go from here to here,
and play the movie

00:48:35.606 --> 00:48:39.840
backwards--What'll happen when
you play the movie backwards?

00:48:39.840 --> 00:48:42.232
Let's say this guy was moving
like this the instant we played

00:48:42.232 --> 00:48:44.672
the movie back.
Well, in the backwards movie it

00:48:44.672 --> 00:48:47.970
started going the other way and
slowly the whole thing will

00:48:47.970 --> 00:48:53.309
untangle itself and end up here.
That also will not happen.

00:48:53.309 --> 00:48:55.820
We all know that if you go to a
room and you release some gas

00:48:55.820 --> 00:48:58.404
from one side,
it can fill the room but it's

00:48:58.404 --> 00:49:02.231
not ever going to come back,
and yet it doesn't violate any

00:49:02.231 --> 00:49:06.059
laws because if I made a movie
and played it backwards,

00:49:06.059 --> 00:49:08.885
in every microscopic
interaction between molecules,

00:49:08.885 --> 00:49:12.050
there'll be no violation of any
of the laws of nature.

00:49:12.050 --> 00:49:15.579
But that doesn't happen.
Here's another thing that

00:49:15.579 --> 00:49:18.132
doesn't happen.
I take a chunk of some hot

00:49:18.132 --> 00:49:21.010
copper and I take a chunk of
some cold copper.

00:49:21.010 --> 00:49:24.495
Hot, cold.
I just put them on top of each

00:49:24.495 --> 00:49:26.863
other, come back in an hour,
it's become,

00:49:26.863 --> 00:49:27.870
say, lukewarm.

00:49:31.330 --> 00:49:33.655
That's fine.
But now maybe,

00:49:33.655 --> 00:49:37.422
if I wait long enough,
the lukewarm will automatically

00:49:37.422 --> 00:49:40.550
spontaneously separate into hot
and cold.

00:49:40.550 --> 00:49:44.986
That doesn't seem to happen.
The heat simply seems to flow

00:49:44.986 --> 00:49:47.860
from hot to cold but never back
from cold to hot.

00:49:47.860 --> 00:49:50.754
But flowing from cold to hot
will not violate the Law of

00:49:50.754 --> 00:49:53.434
Conservation of Energy.
As long as the same number of

00:49:53.434 --> 00:49:56.210
calories go from cold to hot,
it doesn't violate anything.

00:49:56.210 --> 00:49:59.819
And that doesn't seem to happen.
So, this can go on and on and

00:49:59.819 --> 00:50:03.081
on with some large number of
things that are allowed but

00:50:03.081 --> 00:50:06.182
don't happen.
So, we cannot explain them with

00:50:06.182 --> 00:50:10.280
any known laws of physics so we
elevate that to a new law.

00:50:10.280 --> 00:50:12.800
The new law will say these
things cannot happen.

00:50:12.800 --> 00:50:16.150
But you don't have a law that
says these things cannot happen,

00:50:16.150 --> 00:50:17.760
right?
That's not a good enough law.

00:50:17.760 --> 00:50:19.420
You've got to say what things
cannot happen.

00:50:19.420 --> 00:50:21.820
I've got a list a mile long.
Hot and cold,

00:50:21.820 --> 00:50:26.130
when mixed, will never separate
back into hot and cold.

00:50:26.130 --> 00:50:28.277
A gas, that genie that got out
of the bottle,

00:50:28.277 --> 00:50:30.474
won't go back,
there's gas that came out won't

00:50:30.474 --> 00:50:32.196
go back.
There's a whole lot of

00:50:32.196 --> 00:50:34.159
processes which we call
irreversible.

00:50:34.159 --> 00:50:36.110
They never seem to happen
backwards.

00:50:36.110 --> 00:50:40.480
They only happen forwards,
and we cannot list all of them.

00:50:40.480 --> 00:50:43.549
So, you wonder if there's any
law--see, anytime you cannot

00:50:43.549 --> 00:50:46.619
explain something from prior
things, you elevate that to a

00:50:46.619 --> 00:50:48.670
law.
But you like an economical law.

00:50:48.670 --> 00:50:51.278
You would not like a law that
says the following million

00:50:51.278 --> 00:50:55.229
things cannot happen.
And it's really amazing that

00:50:55.229 --> 00:50:58.292
there is one law,
a single law,

00:50:58.292 --> 00:51:02.644
that not only is qualitative,
but is quantitative,

00:51:02.644 --> 00:51:05.788
that tells you exactly when
some things can happen and when

00:51:05.788 --> 00:51:08.999
some things cannot happen,
and according to the one single

00:51:08.999 --> 00:51:12.119
law, all the things that we say
don't happen won't happen.

00:51:12.119 --> 00:51:15.442
Will be forbidden by the law,
and that's a Second law of

00:51:15.442 --> 00:51:18.159
Thermodynamics,
but what form does it take?

00:51:18.159 --> 00:51:21.625
Well, we will see it introduces
a certain quantity called

00:51:21.625 --> 00:51:24.905
entropy, about which let's say
right now we don't know

00:51:24.905 --> 00:51:27.207
anything,
and the law will simply say the

00:51:27.207 --> 00:51:29.429
entropy of the universe will
always increase.

00:51:29.429 --> 00:51:30.920
You don't have to write it down
now.

00:51:30.920 --> 00:51:34.275
I'm going to define the concept.
It'll arise naturally from more

00:51:34.275 --> 00:51:36.992
thinking.
The one law that entropy will

00:51:36.992 --> 00:51:40.079
always increase,
in the universe as a whole,

00:51:40.079 --> 00:51:44.099
is enough to forbid any of
these forbidden processes.

00:51:44.099 --> 00:51:46.416
In other words,
if the paddle spun the other

00:51:46.416 --> 00:51:49.380
way and the weight went up and
the water cooled down,

00:51:49.380 --> 00:51:51.415
you can show the entropy of the
universe would have actually

00:51:51.415 --> 00:51:53.360
gone down.
That's why that's not allowed.

00:51:53.360 --> 00:51:56.417
If you drop a piece of egg,
it comes and splatters all over

00:51:56.417 --> 00:51:59.093
the floor.
If it rejoined and rose back to

00:51:59.093 --> 00:52:03.113
your hand, it won't violate any
other principle other than the

00:52:03.113 --> 00:52:05.729
law of entropy,
because the shattered egg has

00:52:05.729 --> 00:52:08.489
more entropy than the egg that
comes back to your hand.

00:52:08.489 --> 00:52:11.600
And if hot and cold mix to
become lukewarm,

00:52:11.600 --> 00:52:14.860
you can show the entropy goes
up this way,

00:52:14.860 --> 00:52:17.511
but if you went the other way,
entropy will go down and that's

00:52:17.511 --> 00:52:20.116
now allowed.
So, one great law will take

00:52:20.116 --> 00:52:23.612
care of all these things.
So, you've got to ask yourself,

00:52:23.612 --> 00:52:26.300
"What is the one great law and
how do we get to it?"

00:52:26.300 --> 00:52:31.620
Well, it turns out this great
law was discovered by an

00:52:31.620 --> 00:52:36.670
engineer called Carnot.
So, here is another thing.

00:52:36.670 --> 00:52:40.192
People don't wake up and say,
"I'm going to discover a great

00:52:40.192 --> 00:52:42.209
law."
People just go out and do their

00:52:42.209 --> 00:52:45.099
business and all you need is
have enough sense to realize

00:52:45.099 --> 00:52:47.679
when you've stumbled on
something really great.

00:52:47.679 --> 00:52:49.880
So, Carnot had a very practical
question.

00:52:49.880 --> 00:52:54.757
Carnot was working on engines.
At the time they were working

00:52:54.757 --> 00:52:56.690
on something like the steam
engine.

00:52:56.690 --> 00:52:59.920
So, a steam engine--You know
what happens in a steam engine.

00:52:59.920 --> 00:53:02.257
You take some coal,
you set fire to it,

00:53:02.257 --> 00:53:05.210
then you boil some water,
it turns into steam,

00:53:05.210 --> 00:53:08.447
then the steam pushes the
pistons and the wheels turn and

00:53:08.447 --> 00:53:11.570
the train goes forward and
that's your steam engine.

00:53:11.570 --> 00:53:16.110
What happens in a steam engine
we can schematically as follows.

00:53:16.110 --> 00:53:19.205
There is a hot reservoir
T_1 that's the

00:53:19.205 --> 00:53:22.955
furnace of your steam engine.
Then, you have an engine in

00:53:22.955 --> 00:53:26.647
which you've got some steam.
You've got some water that's

00:53:26.647 --> 00:53:29.776
going to be boiled and it's
going to boil only because you

00:53:29.776 --> 00:53:31.848
take in some heat.
Here's my engine,

00:53:31.848 --> 00:53:35.091
it's got some substance inside,
it could be a gasoline engine

00:53:35.091 --> 00:53:37.739
or a steam engine,
we don't care what happens.

00:53:37.739 --> 00:53:41.366
Some amount of heat
Q_1 is taken

00:53:41.366 --> 00:53:45.900
from a hot reservoir and some
amount of work is delivered.

00:53:49.139 --> 00:53:52.150
Now, here is an engine which,
as drawn here,

00:53:52.150 --> 00:53:55.719
doesn't violate any of the laws
of physics, provided

00:53:55.719 --> 00:53:59.570
Q_1 = W,
then energy is conserved.

00:53:59.570 --> 00:54:02.929
In practice you find that's not
how engines work.

00:54:02.929 --> 00:54:05.411
The engine also rejects some
amount of heat

00:54:05.411 --> 00:54:07.892
Q_2 to a lower
temperature

00:54:07.892 --> 00:54:10.651
T_2.
The lower temperature,

00:54:10.651 --> 00:54:13.798
if you look at a steam
engine--if you've gone--Have you

00:54:13.798 --> 00:54:16.739
guys seen a steam engine?
Okay, if you really go see a

00:54:16.739 --> 00:54:19.172
steam engine you will find
there's a lot of hot steam

00:54:19.172 --> 00:54:20.949
coming out of the back or in a
car,

00:54:20.949 --> 00:54:23.090
you've got exhaust gases coming
out.

00:54:23.090 --> 00:54:26.630
That's the hot gas emitted at
atmospheric temperature.

00:54:26.630 --> 00:54:29.489
Inside the engine is a very hot
place.

00:54:29.489 --> 00:54:34.489
So, the car emits some heat at
a lower temperature.

00:54:34.489 --> 00:54:36.869
The steam engine emits some
steam at a lower temperature.

00:54:36.869 --> 00:54:41.365
So, the work that you can get
is really Q_1 -

00:54:41.365 --> 00:54:44.519
Q_2 is what you
can get.

00:54:44.519 --> 00:54:47.639
At least in this engine,
you get Q_1

00:54:47.639 --> 00:54:51.653
and -Q_2.
So, we define a quantity called

00:54:51.653 --> 00:54:55.199
efficiency η.
It's called the efficiency.

00:54:55.199 --> 00:54:58.889
It's what you get divided by
what you pay for.

00:54:58.889 --> 00:55:03.059
You pay for burning the coal
and you get the work out.

00:55:03.059 --> 00:55:05.421
The work is,
of course, the thing that makes

00:55:05.421 --> 00:55:08.313
the engine move forward.
Turns into kinetic energy of

00:55:08.313 --> 00:55:11.481
the locomotive.
That, then, you can see is

00:55:11.481 --> 00:55:14.889
Q_1 -
Q_2.

00:55:14.889 --> 00:55:18.325
What you get divided by what
you pay for, you can write it as

00:55:18.325 --> 00:55:21.590
1 minus Q_2
over Q_1.

00:55:28.989 --> 00:55:33.650
So, in every engine,
some heat is taken in.

00:55:33.650 --> 00:55:38.829
Some of it is converted to work
and some of it is rejected.

00:55:38.829 --> 00:55:41.835
To the extent heat is rejected,
the efficiency is less than 1,

00:55:41.835 --> 00:55:44.446
because Q_2
minus--over Q_1 and is

00:55:44.446 --> 00:55:47.582
subtracted from 1.
So, you can ask yourself why

00:55:47.582 --> 00:55:51.833
not build an engine in which you
just don't reject any heat

00:55:51.833 --> 00:55:54.209
downstairs?
Why not take all the heat and

00:55:54.209 --> 00:55:55.140
convert it to work?

00:55:58.969 --> 00:56:04.339
So, Carnot gave a great
argument on the most efficient

00:56:04.339 --> 00:56:07.485
engine you can build.
In other words,

00:56:07.485 --> 00:56:10.639
there is an upper limit to the
efficiency and it's not 1.

00:56:10.639 --> 00:56:14.780
So, what is it and how are you
going to find out?

00:56:14.780 --> 00:56:18.336
Well, he's going to find out
what it is, but he also needs a

00:56:18.336 --> 00:56:21.137
postulate.
Carnot's postulate is the old

00:56:21.137 --> 00:56:24.360
version of the Second Law of
Thermodynamics.

00:56:24.360 --> 00:56:28.327
He didn't talk about entropy.
You can show in the end they're

00:56:28.327 --> 00:56:30.657
all equivalent,
but Carnot's law,

00:56:30.657 --> 00:56:34.807
which is his own version of the
Second Law, which says the

00:56:34.807 --> 00:56:38.850
following.
So, Law 2 according to Carnot.

00:56:38.850 --> 00:56:44.554
Let me just draw a figure;
then, we'll say

00:56:44.554 --> 00:56:51.199
T_1 is not
allowed.

00:56:51.199 --> 00:56:56.697
Carnot says you cannot build an
engine whose sole effect at the

00:56:56.697 --> 00:57:02.017
end of the day is to transfer
some heat from a cold body to a

00:57:02.017 --> 00:57:05.781
hot body,
whose sole effect--that's very,

00:57:05.781 --> 00:57:15.965
very important.
You cannot have a process whose

00:57:15.965 --> 00:57:22.971
sole effect is this.
I mean, I don't feel like

00:57:22.971 --> 00:57:25.139
writing what this is.
It's what the picture says.

00:57:25.139 --> 00:57:30.514
All right, it doesn't take a
genius to have the heat flow the

00:57:30.514 --> 00:57:32.289
other way.
You understand?

00:57:32.289 --> 00:57:35.085
If you want heat to flow from a
hot body to a cold body,

00:57:35.085 --> 00:57:37.702
that's trivial.
Just connect them with a metal

00:57:37.702 --> 00:57:40.447
rod and it'll flow.
The sole effect of that is

00:57:40.447 --> 00:57:42.570
transfer of heat from hot to
cold.

00:57:42.570 --> 00:57:45.303
That's the way of the natural
order of things,

00:57:45.303 --> 00:57:48.826
but Carnot is saying you can
never build a set of gears and

00:57:48.826 --> 00:57:52.409
wheels and teeth and whatever
you like so that at the end of

00:57:52.409 --> 00:57:55.405
the day,
all that has happened is heat

00:57:55.405 --> 00:57:59.220
has flowed from cold to hot.
That is going to be taken as a

00:57:59.220 --> 00:58:02.003
postulate, and people are
willing to take that as a

00:58:02.003 --> 00:58:04.645
reasonable postulate,
and we want to see what we can

00:58:04.645 --> 00:58:07.289
get out of that postulate.
It turns out it is that

00:58:07.289 --> 00:58:10.803
postulate that's going to
control the efficiency of heat

00:58:10.803 --> 00:58:14.510
engines, put a bound on the
efficiency of heat engines.

00:58:14.510 --> 00:58:19.050
So, don't deduce this.
This is a law.

00:58:19.050 --> 00:58:21.311
Now, you might say,
well, this is how the law

00:58:21.311 --> 00:58:24.395
began, and the law assumed more
and more sophisticated forms,

00:58:24.395 --> 00:58:26.400
so Carnot was not thinking
entropy.

00:58:26.400 --> 00:58:29.150
That came later,
but his postulate was,

00:58:29.150 --> 00:58:32.623
please grant me this,
which seems to be a fact in

00:58:32.623 --> 00:58:34.953
nature.
Then from that let me talk

00:58:34.953 --> 00:58:38.611
about heat engines and show you
that there is an upper limit to

00:58:38.611 --> 00:58:41.413
the efficiency of an engine.
In particular,

00:58:41.413 --> 00:58:45.432
the upper limit is not 1.
It's clear to everybody that

00:58:45.432 --> 00:58:48.924
the limit cannot be more than 1.
If it's more than 1,

00:58:48.924 --> 00:58:51.621
you are taking some amount of
heat and giving even more amount

00:58:51.621 --> 00:58:53.939
of work delivered.
That violates the First Law of

00:58:53.939 --> 00:58:55.980
Thermodynamics.
Conservation of energy.

00:58:55.980 --> 00:58:59.554
But the fact that you must
necessarily reject some heat,

00:58:59.554 --> 00:59:03.260
which you cannot use in this
experiment, is the content of

00:59:03.260 --> 00:59:08.787
Carnot's result.
So, here is the engine that

00:59:08.787 --> 00:59:12.180
Carnot built.
This is called a Carnot engine.

00:59:18.519 --> 00:59:20.449
By the way, look,
don't rely on my graphics.

00:59:20.449 --> 00:59:23.255
I mean, you have to go look at
