01:01:45.032 --> 01:01:48.909
region here and it absorbs heat
in the stage AB.

01:01:48.909 --> 01:01:51.391
It doesn't have any heat
absorption in the state

01:01:51.391 --> 01:01:53.239
BC because it's
adiabatic.

01:01:53.239 --> 01:01:55.638
In CD,
it rejects some heat and

01:01:55.638 --> 01:01:58.489
DA again,
there's no heat transfer.

01:01:58.489 --> 01:02:02.430
So, heat comes in here,
Q_1,

01:02:02.430 --> 01:02:06.550
heat is rejected here,
Q_2.

01:02:06.550 --> 01:02:10.042
If you run the Carnot engine
