01:02:14.719 --> 01:02:17.842
Some work is put in here,
some heat Q_2

01:02:17.842 --> 01:02:20.397
is taken from the lower
reservoir and the heat

01:02:20.397 --> 01:02:22.951
Q_1 is
delivered to the upper

01:02:22.951 --> 01:02:26.080
reservoir.
You know what that gadget is.

01:02:26.080 --> 01:02:30.692
That's a refrigerator.
So, in a refrigerator,

01:02:30.692 --> 01:02:32.855
that's what happens.
You might say hey,

01:02:32.855 --> 01:02:36.112
you violated the Second Law.
You have transferred heat from

01:02:36.112 --> 01:02:38.755
a cold to hot body,
but it was not the only thing

01:02:38.755 --> 01:02:40.792
that happened,
because some compressor

01:02:40.792 --> 01:02:44.159
somewhere did some work.
That's certainly allowed.

01:02:44.159 --> 01:02:48.047
What is not allowed is to have
it flow from cold to hot with

01:02:48.047 --> 01:02:51.842
nothing involved.
The second thing to notice is

01:02:51.842 --> 01:02:56.840
the gas, after doing its thing,
comes back to the starting

01:02:56.840 --> 01:02:59.568
point.
That means you can do it over

01:02:59.568 --> 01:03:02.164
and over and over again.
In one cycle,

01:03:02.164 --> 01:03:04.510
the gas has some heat coming
in.

01:03:04.510 --> 01:03:06.944
Q_1 heat
rejected Q_2,

01:03:06.944 --> 01:03:08.139
some work done,
W,

01:03:08.139 --> 01:03:11.748
and it comes back to where it
is and you can go on doing it

01:03:11.748 --> 01:03:14.989
many, many times.
That's why it's a useful engine.

01:03:14.989 --> 01:03:17.240
If the substance returns to the
starting point,

01:03:17.240 --> 01:03:19.441
having done some work in return
for some heat,

01:03:19.441 --> 01:03:21.300
you can do it over and over
again.

